President Obama has announced his intent to appoint Peter Schaumber to the Board of Trustees of the Christopher Columbus Fellowship Foundation. Schaumber previously served on the National Labor Relations Board (NLRB) and was Chairman from 2008 to 2009. He has also worked as a labor arbitrator, Assistant United States Attorney, and Associate Director of a Law Department division. Schaumber has taught at George Washington University and Georgetown University and was President of the Republican National Lawyers Association. He is a graduate of Georgetown University and Georgetown University Law Center.